  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get a bar graph on Excel to sort from highest to lowest?",
  "response": "To sort a bar graph in Excel from highest to lowest, you need to sort the data that the graph is based on. Here's a step-by-step guide to accomplish this:\n\n1. **Select Your Data**: Click on the range of data that you used to create the bar graph.\n\n2. **Sort the Data**:\n   - Go to the \"Data\" tab on the Excel ribbon.\n   - Click on \"Sort & Filter\" group.\n   - Choose \"Sort Largest to Smallest\" if you're sorting numerical data, or \"Sort A to Z\" if you're sorting text data based on a numerical column.\n\n3. **Select the Column to Sort By**:\n   - In the \"Sort Warning\" dialog box that appears, choose \"Expand the selection\" to ensure that all related data is sorted together.\n   - Click \"Sort\" to proceed.\n\n4. **Update the Graph**:\n   - After sorting the data, the bar graph should automatically update to reflect the new order, showing the bars from highest to lowest.\n\nIf the graph doesn't update automatically:\n\n5. **Refresh the Graph**:\n   - Click on the graph to select it.\n   - Right-click and choose \"Select Data\".\n   - In the \"Select Data Source\" dialog, make sure the data range is correct and click \"OK\".\n\nYour bar graph should now be sorted from highest to lowest based on the values in your data set. If you encounter any issues, ensure that the data range for the graph includes the sorted column and that there are no blank rows or columns disrupting the data continuity.",
